{
  "stem": "11133.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was just-- it was a good feeling, you know, to be able to look the monster in his face.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was even better later on in Poland, when we returned to Poland after the war, to find out that he had been caught, judged guilty, and was facing hanging.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Just what he meted out to other people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the SS-- it was interesting, because the war-- we heard-- we had underground radio that we listened to, so we knew that the war was over on the 7th of May.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But-- and of course, Schindler left under the-- with some of the people who escorted him out of-- into the American zone.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, we were waiting for the Russians to liberate us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were surrounded by the black shirts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were huge groups of them still in the surrounding woods of Czechoslovakia-- or at that area, anyway.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The SS-- from what we understand-- from what I remember, what I understood-- that the two grave-- even though we were under the protection of Schindler, there was a commandant that was in charge of the camp, of the labor camp.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, Schindler only used the labor force in his factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The commandant was supposedly in charge of the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Supposedly, there were two huge graves dug already for us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, I don't know whether that is true or not, that's what I heard.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Schindler-- we also heard that Schindler got the guards drunk in some way, and sent them off on a train, away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "One guard-- and he gave the Jewish policemen guns to protect us while he went away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so, for two days, we had protection from Jewish prisoners holding rifles against any marauders that might be on the outside.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
